reviews.review_text: The fish was scrumptious. I ordered the cod & chips and it came with 2 pieces of cods. The batter was nicely fried and not too thick. I will definitely visit again and try the halibut

Came across here at the public market. It have a large selection of seafood such as calamari, oyster, halibut Got the cod and chips. Pretty crispy and juicy. Price is decent with a good portion of fish and fries. The line is long but it moves quick. Highly recommended.
Really enjoyed the fried oysters here - they were HUGE and so juicy. Clam chowder was nice too.

Ordered the sample platter. Generous portions (our 1 oyster and 1 fish were big enough for 2 people let alone the rest of the goodies on the platter), batter wasn t too thick, was very impressed overall!
I had an excellent cod + chips, very delicious, and I especially liked how quickly it was served (waited only about 2 minutes). Highly recommend their fish and chips!

Very delicious. The halibut is very large, fresh, and tasteful. The fries (chips) are crispy and great. Definitely a great place to eat and enjoy some seafood, especially being around such a lively environment
We really enjoyed our fish and chips. The person at the counter was super nice and we got our plates very fast! Gracias :)

I really enjoyed the halibut. Batter has a nice light colored fry but is still nice and crisp. Fish was flavorful and cooked perfect. Fries werent too bad. They do have a seasoning/condiment tray which I liked.
The best fish & chips I ve ever had. The batter is perfect & the fish is flaky. A must-go-to spot if you re on Granville island!!!
Love the food. Best Fish & Chips that I have had!

The halibut is fresh and flaky, and the crust is deliciously crisp. I am giving this restaurant a 5 star rating, as a tourist, because the portions and quality are far superior to Stevenston fish and chip joints. Come here instead!
Awesome portion and great fresh fish. We had the cod and chips but they were out of coleslaw. Don t understand all the negative comments , cause the lone up was pretty big .
Have only ever ordered chips (I m vegetarian) but they are really tasty and EXCELLENT VALUE. $4.00 for a HUGE plate of fries in Granville island is pretty impressive.
Our fish was perfectly crispy and tender. Cooked to perfection. I would though like to request haddock.
Best Halibut Fish & Chips I found during my stay in the VC area.  Also, best price for that serving size!  Sure wish I could have some more of that right now!
This is a real hidden gem. Not many tourists know this place. Yet, locals know they carry the best fish and chip in Vancouver.
delicious seafood and makes me watering all the time when I remind of its taste.
Best place for fish and chips. Our favourite is the Sampler platter. Totally recommend it.
Nice big portion of Cod and Chips, I also tried the sample platter heafty sized and delicious! Fast service, I would definitely go back!
I was surprised to read these negative reviews, but I loved their fresh and delicious calamari and cod with fries.
Fantastic food!  Be prepared for a long line up, but thats just proof of how great the food is!  Worth the wait!  YUM!
Best deep fried oysters ever.  Worth the calories.
Love this place definitely one of my favorite fish and chips places.
It was really really good but the portion size was massive.
The most delicious Halibut fish n chips.
Enjoyed calamari and fries. I loved it

reviews.review_text: good fish and chips, especially for the price. decent portion size as well. taste is good

Had the halibut fish and chips from this place. The fish was delicious with the tartar sauce. I felt like I had the end of the bag of the fries because the pieces were super small but they were just fries, so it was good nonetheless!
They were sold out of the sampler platter  I really loved the onion rings, everything is made to order
It was good but not perfect. today is Sunday but it s open.

Ive only had a single serving of the salmon & chips at Celines. Given that Granville Island is a bit of a tourist trap, this place is quite reasonable for the portions offered. My salmon fillet had a few bones in it, but that just convinced me that it was real & not some ground up battered patty. If your on the island & hankering for a quick chippie meal, then this is a great option right in the heart of the public market.
Nice fries with fresh fried seafood.Though a bit greasy.
Its a bit pricey but the food is good enough

Some of the best selection for fish and chips in Vancouver as well as great location ....although very busy on the weekend so if you dont like the crowds arrive before closing hours things can wind down by then....Accessibility and friendliness are good and no problem with seating at the Island inside or outdoor areas available.

Honestly I have to disagree with all the negative reviews. The fish we were served tasted great and the only downside was just how busy the location was and how many people were also trying to get their fish and chips
I had the Cod and Chips, taste good but nothing different from the other fish and chips place I have visited
On Granville island, good to grab a quick meal. They do sell bubble tea which is a nice refreshing addition.
A decent experience Kid-friendliness: Good Food : 4/5 |
The chips were good and made fresh there, but the fish pieces were a bit small.
Dry fish. Chips not crisp.

The food came out at a decent time, so I didnt wait as long as expected. The batter on the cod seemed to be a bit too much. The calamari I enjoyed because it wasnt salted like other places. However, I wished I had more tartar sauce. Overall, it was okay.
